===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|ametist|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|ametiste|lang=fro}} (French {{term|améthyste|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἀμέθυστος||not drunk|tr=amethustos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|ἀ-||not|tr=a-|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|μεθύω||I am drunk|tr=methuō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|μέθυ||wine|tr=methu|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}. The Greeks believed that the amethyst prevented [[intoxication]].

